import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller

# Load the data and inspect the first few rows to understand its structure
file_path = 'D:/SCMA632__FIRE632/Stats/Assignment/A6/A6b/CMO-Historical-Data-Monthly.xlsx'
commodity_data_raw = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name='Monthly Prices', skiprows=5)

# Set the correct header from the 5th row
commodity_data_raw.columns = commodity_data_raw.iloc[0]
commodity_data_raw = commodity_data_raw.drop(commodity_data_raw.index[0])

# Rename the first column to 'Date'
commodity_data_raw.rename(columns={commodity_data_raw.columns[0]: 'Date'}, inplace=True)

# Remove 'M' from the date format and convert to datetime
commodity_data_raw['Date'] = commodity_data_raw['Date'].str.replace('M', '')
commodity_data_raw['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(commodity_data_raw['Date'], format='%Y%m', errors='coerce')

# Drop any rows where the date could not be parsed
commodity_data_raw.dropna(subset=['Date'], inplace=True)

# Set 'Date' as the index
commodity_data_raw.set_index('Date', inplace=True)

# Convert all columns to numeric, forcing errors to NaN
commodity_data_raw = commodity_data_raw.apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')

# Drop columns with all NaN values
commodity_data_raw.dropna(axis=1, how='all', inplace=True)

# Drop rows with any NaN values
commodity_data_cleaned = commodity_data_raw.dropna()

# Display the cleaned data
print(commodity_data_cleaned.head())

# Perform the Augmented Dickey-Fuller test on each column
adf_test_results = {}
for column in commodity_data_cleaned.columns:
    if commodity_data_cleaned[column].dtype in [np.float64, np.int64]:
        result = adfuller(commodity_data_cleaned[column].dropna(), autolag='AIC')
        adf_test_results[column] = {
            'Test Statistic': result[0],
            'p-value': result[1],
            'Lags Used': result[2],
            'Number of Observations': result[3],
            'Critical Values': result[4]
        }
    else:
        print(f'Skipping non-numeric column {column}')

# Display the ADF test results
for key, value in adf_test_results.items():
    print(f'ADF Test for {key}:')
    for k, v in value.items():
        print(f'  {k}: {v}')
    print('\n')

# Function to perform ADF test
def adf_test(series):
    result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    return {
        'Test Statistic': result[0],
        'p-value': result[1],
        'Lags Used': result[2],
        'Number of Observations': result[3],
        'Critical Values': result[4]
    }

# Perform ADF test on first differenced data for non-stationary series
first_diff_adf_test_results = {}
for column in commodity_data_cleaned.columns:
    first_diff_series = commodity_data_cleaned[column].diff().dropna()
    result = adf_test(first_diff_series)
    first_diff_adf_test_results[column] = result

# Display the ADF test results for first differenced data
for key, value in first_diff_adf_test_results.items():
    print(f'ADF Test for {key} (First Difference):')
    for k, v in value.items():
        print(f'  {k}: {v}')
    print('\n')

# Identify columns that are stationary at first difference
stationary_at_first_diff = [column for column, result in first_diff_adf_test_results.items() if result['p-value'] < 0.05]

print("Columns stationary at first difference:")
print(stationary_at_first_diff)

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def variance_decomposition(vecm_fit, n_periods=10):
    irf = vecm_fit.irf(n_periods)
    sigma_u = vecm_fit.sigma_u
    n_vars = sigma_u.shape[0]
    fevd = np.zeros((n_periods + 1, n_vars, n_vars))

    for i in range(n_vars):
        for j in range(n_vars):
            fevd[:, i, j] = np.cumsum(irf.orth_irfs[:, j, i]**2) / np.cumsum(irf.orth_irfs[:, :, i].sum(axis=1)**2)

    return fevd

# Perform variance decomposition
n_periods = 10
fevd = variance_decomposition(vecm_fit, n_periods=n_periods)

# Extract number of variables from the VECM model results
n_vars = vecm_fit.neqs
variable_names = vecm_fit.names
time_index = np.arange(n_periods + 1)

# Plot the forecast error variance decomposition for each variable
fig, axes = plt.subplots(n_vars, n_vars, figsize=(12, 12), sharex=True)

for i in range(n_vars):
    for j in range(n_vars):
        axes[i, j].plot(time_index, fevd[:, i, j], label=variable_names[j])
        axes[i, j].set_title(f'{variable_names[i]} variance due to {variable_names[j]}')
        axes[i, j].legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
